{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"dc64d6d260e2683565fe6e13d60cfbe9fec0fa09"},"timestamp":1426203328,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2MDkzNjcyNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/perl-compiler/issues/97","origin":"github"},"title":"methods not found","message":"Original [issue 95](https://code.google.com/p/perl-compiler/issues/detail?id=95) created by rurban on 2012-01-31T22:56:15.000Z:\n\nDeeply nested classes often do not find a parent class method, such as with:\n\n```\nmy $handle = new IO::Socket::SSL;\n$handle-\u0026gt;blocking(0);\n```\n\nwhere the blocking method is implemented by \n  IO::Socket -\u0026gt; IO::Socket::INET -\u0026gt; IO::Socket::SSL.\nAdding intermediate packages previously did not involve storing package data, only package subs via savecv(), so e.g. @IO::Socket::INET::ISA was never stored.\n\nTypical message:\n  -Dp,-v\n  mark threads\n  mark main (forced)\n  main::tid not found\n\nThis was mostly fixed by 17ea6cd8c8eee7 (try_isa) to d0eb89ba9ca5 (@ISA).","files":null}]}